com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution

Class DeviceMappingSnapshot

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution.DeviceMappingSnapshot

  • public class DeviceMappingSnapshot
extends Object
    Contains device information that is used at mapping, for example the information needed for setting the reset flag in the spline motion mapping (first motion, stop condition fired etc).
    This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • isElasticityCompensationSupported

        public boolean isElasticityCompensationSupported()
        Returns:
        true if elasticity compensation is supported, i.e. can be enabled, in the current SPR, provided the device supports elasticity compensation. Elasticity compensation is supported by default. If not supported, e.g. by the control mode, use setElasticityCompensationNotSupported(java.lang.String) to disable it.
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • setElasticityCompensationNotSupported

        public void setElasticityCompensationNotSupported(String reason)
        Sets elasticity compensation as not supported in the current SPR. This method is intended to be used in motion or robot mapper if elasticity compensation is not possible and thus not supported. This can be the case for various reasons, e.g. if the control mode does not support elasticity compensation as in impedance control, or if the motion is performed with an unmastered robot since elasticity compensation requires a valid robot model. Once set to not supported by a mapper, elasticity compensation can not be enabled any more in the current SPR.
        Parameters:
        reason - Reason why elasticity compensation is not supported. Must not be blank.
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • isElasticityCompensationRequested

        public boolean isElasticityCompensationRequested()
        Returns:
        true if elasticity compensation has been requested and shall be enabled in the current SPR, provided the device supports elasticity compensation.
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.
